NO matter how old you are, the death of someone close is a difficult experience. Death can be more challenging on children. Adults push them away from the experience with the intention of sparing them the pain. However, helping children to deal with loss by teaching them the basics can help them to heal. This means having our own emotional houses in order about our own pain and loss. Below are a few tips to help you better support a child: There is no easy way to teach a child how to cope with loss. The best you can do is to equip them with skills by adopting positive coping behaviour in your own life. Send a Please Call Me to 083 323 1023, email mizzb@lovelife.org.za, or into the Facebook page loveLifeNGO.